---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Affiliate Disclosure | Hustle Teacher';
const description = 'Hustle Teacher uses affiliate links. If you click and buy, we may earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. We only recommend products we genuinely believe in.';
import "@/styles/starwind.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" class="dark">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
	</head>
	<body class="bg-background text-foreground scheme-dark min-h-screen flex flex-col">
		<Header />
		<main class="flex-grow docs-site-container border-x">
			<article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
				<h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
				<p class="text-muted-foreground"><strong>Last Updated: March 9, 2026</strong></p>

				<div class="bg-primary/20 border-l-4 border-primary p-4 my-6 rounded-md">
					<strong>⚠️ Transparency Notice:</strong> This website contains affiliate links. If you click on a link and make a purchase,
					we may earn a small commission at no additional cost to you. This helps support our site and keep content free for readers.
				</div>

				<h2>1. What are Affiliate Links?</h2>
				<p>
					Affiliate links are special URLs that track when you click on them and make a purchase. When you buy through our
					affiliate link, the seller (e.g., Amazon, affiliate networks) gives us a small percentage of the sale. You are never
					charged extra — the price is always the same for you.
				</p>

				<h2>2. Which Products Do We Recommend?</h2>
				<p>We include affiliate links for products and services we genuinely believe in, including:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Learning Platforms:</strong> Udemy, Coursera, Skillshare courses</li>
					<li><strong>Software Tools:</strong> Project management, writing, design tools</li>
					<li><strong>Web Hosting & Domains:</strong> Domain registrars, web hosts</li>
					<li><strong>Amazon Products:</strong> Tech, office supplies, books</li>
					<li><strong>Email Marketing:</strong> Mailchimp, Brevo, ConvertKit</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>3. Our Affiliate Networks</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Amazon Associates</li>
					<li>ShareASale</li>
					<li>Impact</li>
					<li>Udemy Affiliate Program</li>
					<li>Skillshare Affiliate Program</li>
					<li>Individual brand affiliate programs</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>4. How We Use Commission Revenue</h2>
				<p>The commissions we earn help us:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Keep the website free for all readers</li>
					<li>Pay for web hosting and domain renewal</li>
					<li>Invest in tools to create better content</li>
					<li>Continue improving the site</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>5. Our Commitment to Honesty</h2>
				<p>We promise to:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>🟢 Only recommend products we genuinely use and believe in</li>
					<li>🟢 Clearly mark affiliate links where possible</li>
					<li>🟢 Never recommend something just for commission</li>
					<li>🟢 Be transparent about our relationships with partners</li>
					<li>🟢 Provide honest reviews, including pros and cons</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>6. Identifying Affiliate Links</h2>
				<p>
					When you hover over links in our content, some may show "affiliate link" or have alternative text. However, not all
					affiliate links are always clearly marked, so it's good practice to assume any product recommendation could be
					affiliated.
				</p>

				<h2>7. FTC Compliance (US)</h2>
				<p>
					This website complies with the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) guidelines on endorsements and testimonials. We
					disclose our affiliate relationships to meet the "Endorsements Guide" requirements set by the FTC.
				</p>
				<p>
					<a href="https://www.ftc.gov/business-guidance/endorsements-testimonials" target="_blank" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 no-underline">
						Read the FTC's Endorsements &amp; Testimonials Guide →
					</a>
				</p>

				<h2>8. Earning Potential</h2>
				<p>
					<strong>Important Note:</strong> Affiliate commissions are typically very small (1-10% of sales). We do not claim
					that affiliate commissions are a significant revenue source or that you will earn money by following our
					recommendations. We share affiliate links purely on merit.
				</p>

				<h2>9. Your Privacy</h2>
				<p>
					When you click an affiliate link, the destination site may place cookies on your device and may collect data about
					your browsing. Please review their privacy policies before making a purchase.
				</p>

				<h2>10. Questions?</h2>
				<p>
					If you have any questions about our affiliate relationships or policies, please contact us at:
					<br />
					<strong>Email:</strong> contact@hustleteacher.com
				</p>

				<hr class="border-t border-border my-8" />

				<p class="text-center text-sm text-muted-foreground">
					<strong>Bottom Line:</strong> We value your trust. We'll never push products just for commission. Our goal is to help you
					make smart decisions and find tools that genuinely improve your online earning journey.
				</p>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
